President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate John Chase Johnson of Oklahoma as the Inspector General at the Federal Communications Commission. Mr. Johnson is an attorney at Covington & Burling LLP, specializing in commercial litigation and government contracts. He is also a Major and Military Judge in the United States Marine Corps Reserves. Prior to joining Covington, Mr. Johnson served on active duty in the United States Marine Corps and was deployed to Afghanistan. He has clerked for Judge Edith Clement of the Fifth Circuit and Judge Victor Wolski of the Court of Federal Claims. Mr. Johnson holds a B.A. in history from Duke University and a J.D. from the University of Virginia School of Law.